and you already want me to leave?

165
00:20:36,291 --> 00:20:40,041
No, I'm just afraid that if he shows up,
I wouldn't know what to tell him.

166
00:20:47,666 --> 00:20:49,375
Do you have money?

167
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:52,541
Yes, I do.

168
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:53,833
Are you sure?

169
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,375
Sure, I'm fine.

170
00:21:05,083 --> 00:21:06,541
-Chon.
-Yes?

171
00:21:07,083 --> 00:21:08,708
Are you thinking straight these days?

172
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:11,125
What do you mean?

173
00:21:12,041 --> 00:21:15,958
No sane person would put a rice cooker
in a fridge. Take it out.

174
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:19,875
Oh, I'm sorry. I forgot.

175
00:21:19,958 --> 00:21:21,208
Are you all right?

176
00:21:21,291 --> 00:21:22,291
I'm fine.

177
00:21:22,666 --> 00:21:24,250
I'm just absent-minded.

178
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:33,250
Do you need help with anything else?

179
00:21:43,583 --> 00:21:45,958
Remove the shell of the prawns
and clean them.

180
00:21:49,458 --> 00:21:50,708
Why don't you do it yourself?

181
00:21:50,833 --> 00:21:52,833
I don't want to commit a sin.

182
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:55,583
Hey, aren't you afraid I'd commit a sin?

183
00:21:57,541 --> 00:21:59,541
You're already a big sinner.

184
00:21:59,625 --> 00:22:02,708
Just do it and stop complaining.

185
00:22:03,166 --> 00:22:04,208
Okay.

186
00:22:04,833 --> 00:22:06,208
Let me ask you a serious question.

187
00:22:06,291 --> 00:22:07,166
What now?

188
00:22:07,541 --> 00:22:08,708
Do bears really eat bees?

189
00:22:09,291 --> 00:22:10,291
I have no idea.

190
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:13,083
Don't they teach you that
in medical school?

191
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:15,583
Do they really eat bees?

192
00:22:15,666 --> 00:22:17,791
-Come on, I really want to know.
-Hey.

193
00:22:17,875 --> 00:22:19,208
Hey, Chon.

194
00:22:19,291 --> 00:22:20,458
If you don't stop talking,

195
00:22:20,541 --> 00:22:23,166
I'll eat you instead.

196
00:22:25,583 --> 00:22:28,000
-So, you don't want the prawns anymore?
-No!

197
00:22:59,541 --> 00:23:00,708
Are you done yet?

198
00:23:02,250 --> 00:23:03,625
Hey, Chon!

199
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:06,958
What did you do, Chon?

200
00:23:08,750 --> 00:23:12,791
-That hurts!
-Be quiet. You're crying like a baby.

201
00:23:21,750 --> 00:23:22,916
What are you looking for?

202
00:23:23,291 --> 00:23:24,791
I'm looking for a needle and a thread.

203
00:23:24,875 --> 00:23:25,791
A needle?

204
00:23:26,333 --> 00:23:28,541
Why do you need it?
Are you going to stitch it up yourself?

205
00:23:28,625 --> 00:23:29,666
Yes.

206
00:23:30,291 --> 00:23:34,500
No! Look at the wound!
Go and get a real doctor to treat me!

207
00:23:34,583 --> 00:23:35,916
I told you not to shout.

208
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:38,125
I'm a doctor. Can't you trust me?

209
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:40,375
Also, stop talking.

210
00:23:41,958 --> 00:23:44,666
Stay here. I'll find a needle
and a thread.

211
00:23:46,541 --> 00:23:49,833
Hey, if somebody finds out,
don't tell them you're with me.

212
00:23:50,125 --> 00:23:51,250
Got it?

213
00:23:52,541 --> 00:23:55,333
Why are you making that face?
"I understand."

214
00:23:55,416 --> 00:23:56,333
Very well.

215
00:24:19,083 --> 00:24:21,083
What are you doing here by yourself?

216
00:24:22,458 --> 00:24:24,375
Oh, what happened to your hand?

217
00:24:25,333 --> 00:24:27,250
Come, let me look at it.

218
00:24:28,916 --> 00:24:31,458
Wow, it's a really deep cut.

219
00:24:31,541 --> 00:24:33,416
Why are you treating it yourself here?

220
00:24:35,125 --> 00:24:35,958
Well...

221
00:24:36,458 --> 00:24:37,458
I...

222
00:24:40,666 --> 00:24:42,541
Do you cook your own meal?

223
00:24:43,791 --> 00:24:44,916
Oh, yes.

224
00:24:45,166 --> 00:24:47,166
I was slicing a prawn.

225
00:24:47,541 --> 00:24:50,500
Maybe it wasn't completely dead,
so it took revenge.

226
00:24:57,583 --> 00:24:58,541
Okay.

227
00:24:58,708 --> 00:24:59,750
I...

228
00:25:00,125 --> 00:25:01,416
Tell me honestly.

229
00:25:02,416 --> 00:25:03,458
So,

230
00:25:04,041 --> 00:25:05,625
which drugs are you on?

231
00:25:09,250 --> 00:25:10,125
Doctor.

232
00:25:10,208 --> 00:25:12,125
I'm not on drugs.

233
00:25:13,250 --> 00:25:15,666
If you don't believe me,
you can test my urine.

234
00:25:15,750 --> 00:25:19,125
My urine, my blood, my hair, anything.
I'm clean. I'm not on drugs.

235
00:25:22,708 --> 00:25:23,958
Excuse me.

236
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,250
Please look at the light.

237
00:25:56,875 --> 00:25:57,958
How many fingers do you see?

238
00:26:00,458 --> 00:26:01,583
One.

239
00:26:04,583 --> 00:26:06,166
Three, maybe.

240
00:26:09,958 --> 00:26:10,916
Please do what I tell you.

241
00:26:12,666 --> 00:26:14,958
Touch the tip of your nose,

242
00:26:15,083 --> 00:26:18,000
and then touch my index finger.
Do it back and forth.

243
00:26:19,041 --> 00:26:20,125
-Like this?
-Yes.

244
00:26:20,333 --> 00:26:21,625
Yes, and touch my finger.

245
00:26:21,833 --> 00:26:22,666
Yes.

246
00:26:22,750 --> 00:26:24,833
-And?
-Touch your nose, back and forth.

247
00:26:26,541 --> 00:26:27,458
Touch here.

248
00:26:29,333 --> 00:26:30,333
Faster, please.

249
00:26:38,083 --> 00:26:40,208
Do you have any other symptoms,

250
00:26:40,458 --> 00:26:43,541
such as insomnia

251
00:26:43,625 --> 00:26:44,708
or hearing things?

252
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:49,875
I don't remember.

253
00:26:50,083 --> 00:26:51,958
Can you remember how many fingers
I just showed you?

254
00:26:52,833 --> 00:26:57,041
Listen, Doc. I was cut by a knife.
I don't think that has anything to do

255
00:26:57,166 --> 00:27:00,375
with counting your fingers
and touching my nose.

256
00:27:04,333 --> 00:27:06,750
Then, please look at your name and tell me
if it's spelled correctly.

257
00:27:06,833 --> 00:27:07,666
CHONLASIT

258
00:27:10,833 --> 00:27:11,833
It's already correct.

259
00:27:14,333 --> 00:27:15,208
Chonlasit.

260
00:27:29,916 --> 00:27:31,333
Please try to talk to this person.

261
00:27:31,958 --> 00:27:33,125
She might be able to help you.

262
00:27:40,958 --> 00:27:42,000
Who's this?

263
00:27:44,083 --> 00:27:45,125
She's a psychiatrist.

264
00:27:51,791 --> 00:27:53,375
I got cut by a knife, Doc.

265
00:28:10,708 --> 00:28:12,708
-Dr. Jib.
-Wait up.

266
00:28:12,791 --> 00:28:16,666
-They need you immediately at ER1.
-Excuse me.

267
00:28:16,750 --> 00:28:17,791
Wait up.

268
00:28:18,875 --> 00:28:19,958
Excuse me.

269
00:28:20,208 --> 00:28:21,333
Please give me a second.

270
00:28:21,416 --> 00:28:24,833
-Please let us through.
-Excuse us.

271
00:28:25,583 --> 00:28:27,958
Please let us through.
It's an emergency case.

272
00:28:28,041 --> 00:28:29,458
This way please, Doctor.

273
00:28:29,625 --> 00:28:31,083
